title: Drawing, "End Tables", ca. 1929–30
markings: Large stamp in black ink, lower right, partially cut off: DONALD DES/145 WEST 57TH ST/NEW YORK C....; small stamp in red ink, lower right: DONALD DESKEY/145 WEST 57TH STREET/NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at center right: END TABLES/SCALE 1"=1'-0"/NUMBER; inscribed dimensions, instructions, materials
description: Elevation drawings for two end tables. Table in upper left with rectangular overall shape, and asymmetrical tubular legs/shelves below surface. Table in lower left with rectangular overall shape and metal strap legs.
